cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about dynamic scene deblurring using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and image priors. The most relevant arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which is the primary focus of the paper. The paper also involves the use of regularization and sparse coding, which are common techniques in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and manipulation, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
